# The portal embeds the SQL migrations via go:embed and validates an Atlas
# checksum (atlas.sum) of them at startup. The checksum is computed over the
# file bytes, so line endings matter: on a machine with core.autocrlf=true these
# .sql files would be checked out as CRLF, the embedded bytes would differ from
# the LF bytes atlas.sum was generated from, and startup fails with
# "validate migrations: checksum mismatch". Pin them to LF on every platform.
internal/store/migrations/*.sql text eol=lf
internal/store/migrations/atlas.sum text eol=lf
